Sentiment Analysis of Amazon AirPods Reviews

Role: Data Analyst / Data Scientist | Tools: R, tidyverse, tm, caret | Techniques: NLP, Text Mining, Machine Learning

Project Summary

Performed sentiment analysis on Amazon AirPods customer reviews to classify feedback as positive, negative, or neutral, providing actionable insights for product improvement, marketing strategy, and customer experience optimization.

Key Contributions & Skills Demonstrated

Data Collection & Preprocessing

Collected 10,000+ Amazon reviews and labeled sentiments (positive, negative, neutral).

Cleaned text data by removing stop words, punctuation, and numbers.

Applied tokenization, stemming, lemmatization, and vectorization (TF-IDF) to prepare data for modeling.

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Explored sentiment distribution and identified common phrases using word clouds and bar charts.

Uncovered patterns in customer feedback to highlight product strengths and pain points.

Machine Learning Modeling

Built Naive Bayes and Random Forest classifiers to predict sentiment.

Evaluated models using accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.

Visualized model performance with confusion matrices and sentiment distribution plots.

Insights & Business Impact

Positive sentiments associated with words like “great”, “excellent”, “amazing”; negative with “poor”, “worst”, “bad”.

Identified areas for product improvement and highlighted key features appreciated by customers.

Enabled data-driven recommendations for marketing campaigns, customer support strategies, and product development.

Tools & Techniques

Programming & Libraries: R, tidyverse, tm, wordcloud, caret

NLP & Text Mining: Tokenization, Stemming, Lemmatization, TF-IDF

Machine Learning: Naive Bayes, Random Forest

Visualization: Word clouds, Bar charts, Confusion matrices

Outcome / Impact

Achieved ~91% accuracy in classifying customer sentiments.

Provided actionable insights for enhancing customer satisfaction and optimizing marketing strategies.

Demonstrated strong capability in text analytics, NLP, and translating data into business decisions, applicable to VoC, CX, and Data Analyst roles.
